description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This Vacancy &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to expansion of the service, we are looking to recruit additional RA Planners to work within Community Intermediate Care Service (CICS). You will work within an office based team who plan and coordinate care for patients within their own homes. Your role within that team will be to schedule care calls for the RAs to both Active Recovery and Stroke patients using an electronic system. You will be responsible for the entry of patient data ensuring that appropriate care is delivered to patients by the most appropriate member of staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CICS support patients by providing care and clinical support at home to avoid hospital admission or facilitate discharge from hospital. It is a citywide service made up of a multi-disciplinary team; consisting of Nurses, Physiotherapists, Occupational Therapists, other specialist therapists, Pharmacists, Rehabilitation Assistants, Admin support and Managers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service operates from 6am to 12am,7 days per week, including all Bank Holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are looking for&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and organised individual who is logical in their approach to a challenge. You must have attributes that include resilience and be proactive.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have experience of working within a health service and be competent in IT related tasks and systems. It is desirable that you will have experience of scheduling work for a team however, this is not essential as full training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role is highly responsive to changing demands for care and you therefore need to be flexible to meet this demand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will be expected to cover&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;shifts from 6am to 8pm, 365 days a year including weekends and Bank Holidays.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
